Model Specific Description: This field is used to indicate the actor by whom the alternate name attributed to the instance of event is/was used.
This field is used to indicate an identifier attributed to the documented event.
This field is used to indicate the type of an identifier attributed to the documented event.
This field is used to indicate the institution providing the documented event its ID.
This field is used to indicate the source based on which the identifier was attributed to the documented event.
This field is used to indicate the main name attributed to the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the language of the name attributed to the documented event.
This field is used to indicate the formal type of event a documented instance of event is classified as.
This field is used to indicate additional names under which the documented instance of event is known. This can be linked to the additional name type and earliest and latest date of use of that name.
This field is used to indicate the type of alternative name that is attributed to the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the language of the alternative name attributed to the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the earliest known date for use of an alternative name for the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the latest known date for use of an alternative name for the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the organization or individual attributing the alternative name to the documented instance of event.
This field is used to indicate the actor by whom the alternative name attributed to the instance of event is/was used.
